We take pleasure in presenting “Carrol Boyes - The Inside Story” – a comprehensive video study of the woman and her creative team behind the brand. www.carrolboyes.com JOHANNESBURG - Acclaimed South African artist Carrol Boyes has died following a short illness. Boyes was the founder, creator and CEO of The Carrol Boyes retailer in Cape Town. READ: SA musician Johnny Clegg has died The company confirmed the news of her death in a statement released on Thursday, saying: "South Africa mourns the death of Iconic Artist and Designer, Carrol Boyes." "We are saddened by the loss of Carrol, who passed away last night after a brief illness." She founded her company in 1991 and her products were available in over 30 other countries around the world.